**\n1. Address WARN items from validation report\n2. Create tasklist and assign to implementer subagent\n3. Proceed to implementation\n\n---\n\n**AIDD:READ_LOG:**\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/plan/TST-001-validation.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/reports/context/TST-001.pack.md`\n\n**AIDD:ACTIONS_LOG:**\n- Reviewed plan against PRD requirements\n- Validated research alignment and technology adaptations\n- Assessed risk register completeness\n- Evaluated test coverage plan\n- Identified 3 WARN items requiring attention\n- Approved plan with conditions"}],"totalDurationMs":63102,"totalTokens":38114,"totalToolUseCount":10,"usage":{"input_tokens":8914,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":27648,"output_tokens":1552,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_ZNBCWklsCYWAa1bWKWaljSXJ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have all the necessary information to perform a comprehensive PRD review. Let me analyze the PRD against the research findings and provide a structured review.\n\nBased on my analysis of the PRD and research findings, here is the structured PRD Review:\n\n---\n\n## PRD Review Report — TST-001 (fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement)\n\n**Status:** NEEDS_REVISION  \n**Reviewer:** PRD Review Agent  \n**Date:** 2026-03-18  \n**Files Reviewed:**\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/reports/context/TST-001.pack.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md`\n\n---\n\n### Summary Assessment\n\nThe PRD contains well-structured requirements for implementing live RBAC enforcement, audit logging, and frontend synchronization. However, **critical discrepancies exist between the PRD assumptions and the actual codebase state** identified in research. The PRD assumes JWT-based authentication and Redux state management, while the research reveals header-based authentication (X-Profile-Key) and Zustand state management. These mismatches must be resolved before implementation can proceed.\n\n---\n\n### Critical Findings\n\n| Finding | Severity | Description | Recommendation |\n|---------|----------|-------------|----------------|\n| **F1: Authentication Model Mismatch** | **CRITICAL** | PRD states \"custom middleware on JWT-claims\" (Q2=B), but research found no JWT infrastructure. System uses `X-Profile-Key` and `X-Profile-Auth` headers. | Update PRD to reflect header-based auth model. Revise Q2 answer and all JWT references. |\n| **F2: State Management Mismatch** | **CRITICAL** | PRD specifies \"React + Context/Redux\" (Q3=A), but research found Zustand is used (`profileStore.ts`). | Update PRD to reflect Zustand usage. Revise frontend sync requirements accordingly. |\n| **F3: WebSocket vs SSE Gap** | **HIGH** | PRD requires WebSocket push-updates (Q5=A), but research found SSE infrastructure already exists. WebSocket requires new dependencies. | Evaluate SSE extension vs WebSocket implementation. Document decision rationale. |\n| **F4: Missing Spring Security** | **HIGH** | PRD assumes RBAC middleware can integrate with existing security, but no Spring Security found in classpath. | Add dependency requirement to PRD. Document security filter implementation approach. |\n| **F5: No Audit Log Schema** | **MEDIUM** | PRD requires audit logs in DB, but no `audit_log` table exists. | Add database migration requirement to implementation plan. |\n| **F6: Incomplete Roll-out Section** | **LOW** | Section 7 (AIDD:ROLL_OUT) is empty placeholder. | Define rollout phases, feature flags, and rollback strategy. |\n\n---\n\n### Open Questions Requiring Clarification\n\n**Question 1 (Blocker):** Should RBAC enforcement use Spring Security filters or custom WebFlux filters?  \n**Why:** Spring Security is not currently in the classpath. This decision impacts dependency management and implementation complexity.  \n**Options:**  \nA) Add `spring-boot-starter-security` and use Spring Security filters  \nB) Implement custom WebFlux filters without Spring Security  \nC) Use method-level annotations with a lightweight security library  \n**Default:** A  \n\n**Question 2 (Blocker):** Should role synchronization use existing SSE infrastructure or implement new WebSocket?  \n**Why:** SSE already exists for flows/MCP; WebSocket requires new infrastructure but provides bidirectional communication.  \n**Options:**  \nA) Extend existing SSE for role change notifications  \nB) Implement new WebSocket infrastructure as specified in PRD  \nC) Use polling fallback with configurable interval  \n**Default:** A  \n\n**Question 3 (Clarification):** How should backend fetch profile roles for RBAC checks?  \n**Why:** Roles are stored in profile documents. Need to determine caching strategy to meet P95 ≤ 10ms latency requirement.  \n**Options:**  \nA) Call profile service on each request (no cache)  \nB) In-memory cache with TTL (as mentioned in PRD risks)  \nC) Distributed cache (Redis) for multi-instance deployments  \n**Default:** B  \n\n**Question 4 (Clarification):** What is the source of truth for role definitions?  \n**Why:** Need to clarify if roles are managed in profile service only or if local RBAC tables are needed.  \n**Options:**  \nA) Profile service is the only source of truth  \nB) Local RBAC tables with sync from profile service  \nC) Hybrid: profile service for storage, local cache for enforcement  \n**Default:** C  \n\n---\n\n### AIDD:READ_LOG\n\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md` — Full PRD document (259 lines)\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/reports/context/TST-001.pack.md` — Context pack (24 lines)\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md` — Research findings (280 lines)\n\n---\n\n### Verdict: **NEEDS_REVISION**\n\nThe PRD requires updates to align with actual codebase state before implementation can proceed. Critical mismatches in authentication model (JWT vs header-based) and state management (Redux vs Zustand) must be resolved. Open questions regarding Spring Security adoption and SSE vs WebSocket need stakeholder decisions.\n\n**Required Actions Before READY Status:**\n1. Update Q2 answer to reflect header-based authentication\n2. Update Q3 answer to reflect Zustand state management\n3. Resolve Q5 (WebSocket vs SSE) based on architectural decision\n4. Document Spring Security dependency requirement\n5. Define audit_log table schema in requirements\n6. Complete AIDD:ROLL_OUT section with deployment strategy\n\n---\n\n### Updated PRD Review Section\n\n```markdown\n## 11. PRD Review\nStatus: NEEDS_REVISION\n\n### Summary\nPRD requires alignment with actual codebase state. Research revealed header-based auth (not JWT) and Zustand (not Redux). Critical architectural decisions needed on Spring Security adoption and SSE vs WebSocket.\n\n### Findings\n- [ ] F1: Authentication model mismatch (JWT assumed, headers actual) — CRITICAL — Update PRD Q2 and all JWT references\n- [ ] F2: State management mismatch (Redux assumed, Zustand actual) — CRITICAL — Update PRD Q3 and frontend sync requirements\n- [ ] F3: WebSocket requirement conflicts with existing SSE infrastructure — HIGH — Document architectural decision\n- [ ] F4: Spring Security dependency missing from classpath — HIGH — Add to requirements\n- [ ] F5: No audit_log table exists — MEDIUM — Add migration requirement\n- [ ] F6: Roll-out section incomplete — LOW — Define deployment strategy\n\n### Action items\n- [ ] Update PRD Q2 to reflect header-based auth (X-Profile-Key) — Analyst — 2026-03-18\n- [ ] Update PRD Q3 to reflect Zustand state management — Analyst — 2026-03-18\n- [ ] Resolve SSE vs WebSocket decision — Architect — 2026-03-19\n- [ ] Document Spring Security dependency — Analyst — 2026-03-18\n- [ ] Define audit_log schema — DBA/Analyst — 2026-03-19\n- [ ] Complete AIDD:ROLL_OUT section — PM/Analyst — 2026-03-19\n\n> Обновите статус на `READY`, когда все пункты закрыты.\n```"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a512d44ba97b8ec87 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 21699\ntool_uses: 8\nduration_ms: 81987</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"386f7333-beca-450a-9559-9ee7ee33b01e","uuid":"f06e8830-ea5e-4bf7-9ac1-6d7f54e6222d","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Review the PRD for ticket TST-001 (fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement).\n\nContext:\n- Ticket: TST-001\n- Slug: fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\n- PRD: aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md\n\nYour task is to perform a structural review of the PRD:\n1. Check for completeness of requirements\n2. Identify ambiguity or missing details\n3. Verify acceptance criteria are testable\n4. Assess risks and technical constraints\n\nRead the PRD file, then provide a structured review report with:\n- Summary assessment\n- Critical findings (if any)\n- Open questions that need clarification\n- Verdict (ready / needs revision / blocked)","agentId":"a512d44ba97b8ec87","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have all the necessary information to perform a comprehensive PRD review. Let me analyze the PRD against the research findings and provide a structured review.\n\nBased on my analysis of the PRD and research findings, here is the structured PRD Review:\n\n---\n\n## PRD Review Report — TST-001 (fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement)\n\n**Status:** NEEDS_REVISION  \n**Reviewer:** PRD Review Agent  \n**Date:** 2026-03-18  \n**Files Reviewed:**\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/reports/context/TST-001.pack.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md`\n\n---\n\n### Summary Assessment\n\nThe PRD contains well-structured requirements for implementing live RBAC enforcement, audit logging, and frontend synchronization. However, **critical discrepancies exist between the PRD assumptions and the actual codebase state** identified in research. The PRD assumes JWT-based authentication and Redux state management, while the research reveals header-based authentication (X-Profile-Key) and Zustand state management. These mismatches must be resolved before implementation can proceed.\n\n---\n\n### Critical Findings\n\n| Finding | Severity | Description | Recommendation |\n|---------|----------|-------------|----------------|\n| **F1: Authentication Model Mismatch** | **CRITICAL** | PRD states \"custom middleware on JWT-claims\" (Q2=B), but research found no JWT infrastructure. System uses `X-Profile-Key` and `X-Profile-Auth` headers. | Update PRD to reflect header-based auth model. Revise Q2 answer and all JWT references. |\n| **F2: State Management Mismatch** | **CRITICAL** | PRD specifies \"React + Context/Redux\" (Q3=A), but research found Zustand is used (`profileStore.ts`). | Update PRD to reflect Zustand usage. Revise frontend sync requirements accordingly. |\n| **F3: WebSocket vs SSE Gap** | **HIGH** | PRD requires WebSocket push-updates (Q5=A), but research found SSE infrastructure already exists. WebSocket requires new dependencies. | Evaluate SSE extension vs WebSocket implementation. Document decision rationale. |\n| **F4: Missing Spring Security** | **HIGH** | PRD assumes RBAC middleware can integrate with existing security, but no Spring Security found in classpath. | Add dependency requirement to PRD. Document security filter implementation approach. |\n| **F5: No Audit Log Schema** | **MEDIUM** | PRD requires audit logs in DB, but no `audit_log` table exists. | Add database migration requirement to implementation plan. |\n| **F6: Incomplete Roll-out Section** | **LOW** | Section 7 (AIDD:ROLL_OUT) is empty placeholder. | Define rollout phases, feature flags, and rollback strategy. |\n\n---\n\n### Open Questions Requiring Clarification\n\n**Question 1 (Blocker):** Should RBAC enforcement use Spring Security filters or custom WebFlux filters?  \n**Why:** Spring Security is not currently in the classpath. This decision impacts dependency management and implementation complexity.  \n**Options:**  \nA) Add `spring-boot-starter-security` and use Spring Security filters  \nB) Implement custom WebFlux filters without Spring Security  \nC) Use method-level annotations with a lightweight security library  \n**Default:** A  \n\n**Question 2 (Blocker):** Should role synchronization use existing SSE infrastructure or implement new WebSocket?  \n**Why:** SSE already exists for flows/MCP; WebSocket requires new infrastructure but provides bidirectional communication.  \n**Options:**  \nA) Extend existing SSE for role change notifications  \nB) Implement new WebSocket infrastructure as specified in PRD  \nC) Use polling fallback with configurable interval  \n**Default:** A  \n\n**Question 3 (Clarification):** How should backend fetch profile roles for RBAC checks?  \n**Why:** Roles are stored in profile documents. Need to determine caching strategy to meet P95 ≤ 10ms latency requirement.  \n**Options:**  \nA) Call profile service on each request (no cache)  \nB) In-memory cache with TTL (as mentioned in PRD risks)  \nC) Distributed cache (Redis) for multi-instance deployments  \n**Default:** B  \n\n**Question 4 (Clarification):** What is the source of truth for role definitions?  \n**Why:** Need to clarify if roles are managed in profile service only or if local RBAC tables are needed.  \n**Options:**  \nA) Profile service is the only source of truth  \nB) Local RBAC tables with sync from profile service  \nC) Hybrid: profile service for storage, local cache for enforcement  \n**Default:** C  \n\n---\n\n### AIDD:READ_LOG\n\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md` — Full PRD document (259 lines)\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/reports/context/TST-001.pack.md` — Context pack (24 lines)\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md` — Research findings (280 lines)\n\n---\n\n### Verdict: **NEEDS_REVISION**\n\nThe PRD requires updates to align with actual codebase state before implementation can proceed. Critical mismatches in authentication model (JWT vs header-based) and state management (Redux vs Zustand) must be resolved. Open questions regarding Spring Security adoption and SSE vs WebSocket need stakeholder decisions.\n\n**Required Actions Before READY Status:**\n1. Update Q2 answer to reflect header-based authentication\n2. Update Q3 answer to reflect Zustand state management\n3. Resolve Q5 (WebSocket vs SSE) based on architectural decision\n4. Document Spring Security dependency requirement\n5. Define audit_log table schema in requirements\n6. Complete AIDD:ROLL_OUT section with deployment strategy\n\n---\n\n### Updated PRD Review Section\n\n```markdown\n## 11. PRD Review\nStatus: NEEDS_REVISION\n\n### Summary\nPRD requires alignment with actual codebase state. Research revealed header-based auth (not JWT) and Zustand (not Redux). Critical architectural decisions needed on Spring Security adoption and SSE vs WebSocket.\n\n### Findings\n- [ ] F1: Authentication model mismatch (JWT assumed, headers actual) — CRITICAL — Update PRD Q2 and all JWT references\n- [ ] F2: State management mismatch (Redux assumed, Zustand actual) — CRITICAL — Update PRD Q3 and frontend sync requirements\n- [ ] F3: WebSocket requirement conflicts with existing SSE infrastructure — HIGH — Document architectural decision\n- [ ] F4: Spring Security dependency missing from classpath — HIGH — Add to requirements\n- [ ] F5: No audit_log table exists — MEDIUM — Add migration requirement\n- [ ] F6: Roll-out section incomplete — LOW — Define deployment strategy\n\n### Action items\n- [ ] Update PRD Q2 to reflect header-based auth (X-Profile-Key) — Analyst — 2026-03-18\n- [ ] Update PRD Q3 to reflect Zustand state management — Analyst — 2026-03-18\n- [ ] Resolve SSE vs WebSocket decision — Architect — 2026-03-19\n- [ ] Document Spring Security dependency — Analyst — 2026-03-18\n- [ ] Define audit_log schema — DBA/Analyst — 2026-03-19\n- [ ] Complete AIDD:ROLL_OUT section — PM/Analyst — 2026-03-19\n\n> Обновите статус на `READY`, когда все пункты закрыты.\n```"}],"totalDurationMs":81987,"totalTokens":21699,"totalToolUseCount":8,"usage":{"input_tokens":5420,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":14592,"output_tokens":1687,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0